Continental Federal Savings andLoan Association said it was told that an estate holding 38 pctof its stock plans to sell its stake at a premium over thecurrent stock price.   Continental said the estate of Harold Vernon and certainparties have signed a letter of intent to sell the stock for12.25 dlrs a share, for a total of about 6,538,000 dlrs.Continental's stock closed at seven in over-the-countertrading.    The thrift said the buyer is &lt;BAC Inc>, a corporationacting for certain unindentified parties. Reuter&#3;